*                          FILE: FRM_DWG.SIZ
*============================================================================
*    mbs                      Metric file   
*   This file provides options for preparing the rigid frame shop 
*   drawings. The file is read by the rigid frame detailing program and 
*   each of the rigid frame shop drawings. To change the appearance of 
*   the shop drawing, the user needs to edit this file. 
*
*   The file starts with those items that apply to all drawings then has 
*   a section on each of the four types of drawings: web, interior 
*   columns, plates, and assembly. Each drawing section starts with a 
*   drawing layout, user details, and concludes with drawing options. 
*   There are a number of additional lines for each type of drawing for 
*   future drawing options. The remainder of this help file describes 
*   the input data.
*
*   In this description the job Id is taken as 12345. Some name options 
*   use all 5 numbers, others use the last 3 numbers.
*
*(1) GENERAL OPTIONS:
*   Id
*   1 to 4  Select options 1 to 5 for each item based on the table shown 
*           below. The names are illustrated for the outside flange, OF.
*
*           Option     Fabricated piece 1    Fabricated piece 2 
*              1        OF1       OF2         OF1       OF2
*              2        OF1-RF1-1             OF1-RF1-1
*              3        OF1       OF2         OF3       OF4
*              4        OF1-456   OF2-456     OF3-456   OF4-456
*              5        12345OF1  12345OF2    12345OF3  12345OF4
*
*   5             These names are used to identify the fabricated piece 
*                 and will be used in all references to that piece.
*
*(2) (5) (8) (11) DRAWING LAYOUT:
*      PAGE SIZE: Enter the size of the page for the shop drawing.
*      OFFSET: Enter the distance from the four sides of the drawing to 
*              the plan view of the fabricated piece.
*      SCALE FACTORS: Enter scale factors for the piece, text, tables, 
*              dimension line offset, and title block. The piece scale 
*              factor can range from 1 to 5. At 1, the horizontal and 
*              vertical scales are equal. At 5, the vertical scale is 5 
*              times the horizontal scale. 
*      LOGO: Enter Y if a customized logo is to be used. The logo for 
*              different drawings must be stored in the C:\MBS\BLK 
*              subdirectory and stored under the following names: 
*              ASM_LOGO.BLK, WEB_LOGO.BLK, and INT_LOGO.BLK
*
*
*(3) (6) (9) (12) USER DETAILS:
*      NUMBER OF DETAILS: Enter the number of user prepared details which 
*              will appear on the drawing.
*      DETAIL ID: Enter the name of the detail, for example 'WEBA'. The 
*              detail must be stored in the C:\MBS\BLK subdirectory under 
*              the name WEBA.BLK.
*      LOCATION: Enter the x and y coordinates for the insert point on 
*              the detail. The origin for the coordinates is at the lower 
*              left corner of the drawing.
*      SCALE: Enter the scale factor used to adjust the size of the 
*              detail. For example if the detail was drawn as 3" by 4" 
*              and you want to show the detail as 1.5" by 2", enter a 
*              scale factor of 0.50.
*      THIS FEATURE CAN BE USED TO MOVE PROGRAM GENERATED BLOCKS:
*           1. Use the block names shown on drawings, ASM and WEB.
*           2. Use the location coordinates to place the block insert 
*              point at the desired location on the drawing.
*
*
*(1)GENERAL OPTIONS:
*
*Option  Id  DWG  Description
*------  --  ---  --------------------------------------------------------------
  '3'     1       Web Part: See above.
  '3'     2       Flg Part: See above.
  '3'     3       EP  Part: See above.
  '3'     4       ST EC Part: See above.
  '1'     5       Piece Id: (1)=RF1-1, (2)RF1-1-345 (3)12345-RF1-1
  '3'     6       Web Part: See above, Rigid Frame fully scaled drawings.(3-5)
  '3'     7       Flg Part: See above, Rigid Frame fully scaled drawings.(3-5)
  '3'     8       EP  Part: See above, Rigid Frame fully scaled drawings.(3-5)
  '3'     9       ST EC Part: See above, Rigid Frame fully scaled drawings.(3-5)
  '-'    10       Open
  '3'    11       Web Part: See above,   CWI fully scaled drawings, (3-5)
  '3'    12       Flg Part: See above, CWI fully scaled drawings, (3-5)
  '3'    13       EP  Part: See above, CWI fully scaled drawings, (3-5)
  '3'    14       ST EC Part: See above, CWI fully scaled drawings, (3-5)
  '-'    15
  '-'    16
  '-'    17
  '-'    18
  '-'    19
  '-'    20


