*(4)WEB DRAWING OPTIONS:
*
*Option  Id  DWG   Description
*------  --  ---  -----------
  '-'     1       Not used.
  '8'     2       Dimensions on dwgs: 1=in.dec, 2=ft-in-frc, 3=ft.dec, 4=in-frc
  '8'     3       Units on thickness: same as 2.
  '2'     4       Thickness: (1)=gage, (2)=normal thickness 
  '1'     5       Dimensioning: (1)=Arrows, (2)=Tick Marks
  '1'     6       Show double web piece (1), single web piece(2)
  '2'     7 WEB1  Hor dim to inside cor of col web:(1)=No,(2)=Hor,(3)=Hor
  '2'     8 WEB1  Ver dim to inside cor of col web:(1)=Ver,(2)=Diag&Ver,(3)=Ver
  '1'     9 WEB1  web assm:(1)web pieces only,(2)show flg size @ edge of web
  '1'    10 WEB1  Show slot/hole&dim(1),show slots(2&4),no slots(3),sho&Lbl(5)
  '3'    11 WEB2  show rise per foot on cutline:(1)=Yes, (2)=No 
  '1'    12 WEB2  Web hole/slot dim start at:(1)=Fab web, (2)=Individual web
  '2'    13 WEB2  To show on drawing:1=jobId & WB1, 2=WB1 only.
  '5'    14 WEB2  Horizontal cut dimensions:1=show on bottom, 2=show on top
  '-'    15 
  '-'    16 WEB2  '2' if a detail of the web holes id shown on the WEB dwg.
  '-'    17
  '2'    18 ASM3  Draw end slopes (1)=yes, (2)=no,(3)=end slope with degrees 
  '-'    19
  '-'    20

