*(7)INTERIOR COLUMN DRAWING OPTIONS:
*
*Option  Id   DWG   Description
*------  --  -----  -----------
  '8'     1         Dimensions on dw: 1=in.dec, 2=ft-in-frc, 3=ft.dec, 4=in-frc
  '8'     2         Dimensions in material list table: as in 1.
  '2'     3         Plate table wts. and quantities:(1)=by bldg,(2)by fab piece
  '2'     4         Use material codes:(1)=yes (2)=no
  '1'     5  INT1   Plate location dimensioned to:(1)=end of pl,(2)=cen of hole
  '_'     6  INT1   Length of tube: (1)=w/ outside dim., (2)=decimal feet
  '2'     7         Plate thickness as: (1)=gage, (2)=fraction
  '1'     8  INT1   Cut at top reported as: (1)=cut, (2)=angle
  '1'     9         Arrows or Tick Marks: 1=Arrows, else=Tick Marks
  '2'    10  INT1   Report weight by building(1) or by part(2)
  '2'    11         '2' places FAB LEN in title block, else CUT LEN.
  '2'    12         '2' to draw and lablel CUT LEN, else not given.
  '2'    13         To add TAPE(2) or TAIL(3) label for dim along either flange.
  '2'    14         Hor lines in member table: '2' = use, else do not use.
  '-'    15         Hole loc on outside flange measured from:1= Fab end, 2=stock end 
  '-'    16         Len dim on column IS flg and BEP:1=none,2=indiv dim,3=combined
  '2'     17  INT1     '1'= end plate dimensioned in detail, '2'= end plate dimensioned on member
  '1'     18           Remove std details when clip sub is used (1) show all, (2) remove std details
  '1'     19       '2' = display weld symbols(need weld sizes in DS_WELD file, see PE 11-01-2),'3' Weld Table
  '-'    20


